sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor Dev as Developer
    participant SSH as OpenSSH<br/>(ssh / scp / sftp)
    participant Socket as Agent Socket<br/>(Unix / Named Pipe)
    participant Parser as Protocol Parser
    participant Policy as Policy Engine<br/>(allowed_labels)
    participant Backend as sshenc-se<br/>(SshencBackend)
    participant Lib as libenclaveapp
    participant SE as Secure Element<br/>(SE / TPM)
    participant Remote as SSH Server

    Dev->>SSH: ssh user@host (or git push)
    SSH->>SSH: Read ~/.ssh/config (IdentityAgent)

    SSH->>Socket: SSH_AGENTC_REQUEST_IDENTITIES
    Socket->>Parser: parse message
    Parser->>Backend: list public keys
    Backend->>Backend: read ~/.sshenc/keys/*.pub
    Backend-->>Parser: public key list
    Parser-->>Socket: SSH_AGENT_IDENTITIES_ANSWER
    Socket-->>SSH: available public keys

    SSH->>Remote: TCP connect + key exchange
    Remote-->>SSH: server hello + challenge

    SSH->>Socket: SSH_AGENTC_SIGN_REQUEST (key_blob, data)
    Socket->>Parser: parse sign request

    Parser->>Policy: check key label against allowed_labels

    alt Key not in allowed_labels
        Policy-->>Parser: DENY
        Parser-->>Socket: SSH_AGENT_FAILURE
        Socket-->>SSH: sign refused
    else Key allowed
        Policy-->>Parser: ALLOW

        opt User-presence policy requires prompt
            Parser->>Dev: Touch ID / Hello / platform prompt
            Dev-->>Parser: biometric confirmed
        end

        Parser->>Backend: sign(key_handle, data, flags)
        Backend->>Lib: ECDSA P-256 sign
        Lib->>SE: hardware sign operation
        SE-->>Lib: raw ECDSA signature (r, s)
        Lib-->>Backend: signature bytes
        Backend-->>Parser: SSH signature blob

        Parser-->>Socket: SSH_AGENT_SIGN_RESPONSE
        Socket-->>SSH: signature
    end

    SSH->>Remote: signed authentication response
    Remote-->>SSH: authentication success
    SSH-->>Dev: connected / push complete

    Note over SSH,SE: Private key material NEVER leaves the Secure Element.<br/>Only public keys and signatures cross the agent boundary.
